
OpenCICM: Open Common Interface to Cryptographic Modules
========================================================


CICM -- pronounced Kick-Em -- is a programming interface to standardize
the way software programs manage and use high assurance crypto modules.

Written in Erlang, OpenCICM is aimed at supporting with running code
the CICM undergoing standardization activities by the IETF.



Specification Documents
-----------------------

- CICM <http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-lanz-cicm>
- Logical Model <http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-lanz-cicm-lm>
- Module Management <http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-lanz-cicm-mm>
- Key Management <http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-lanz-cicm-km>
- Channel Management <http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-lanz-cicm-cm>



